{{Infobox person | name = Caroline Dries | image = Caroline Dries by Gage Skidmore.jpg | caption = Dries in 2015 | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[United States]] | occupation = [[Television writer]], [[Television producer|producer]] | yearsactive = 2006&ndash;present }}
'''Caroline Dries''' is an American [[television writer]] and [[television producer|producer]] who has worked as a writer on three series for [[The CW]]; ''[[Smallville (TV series)|Smallville]]'', ''[[Melrose Place (2009 TV series)|Melrose Place]]'' and served as an executive producer on ''[[The Vampire Diaries]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.film.com/celebrities/caroline-dries/14685699|title=Caroline Dries from Melrose Place|work=Film.com|accessdate=January 6, 2011}}</ref> She is also known for the footage she captured of the 9/11 terrorist attacks on NYC.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_qiVBOqNiOs |title=Student shoots video of WTC on 9/11|work=youtube.com|accessdate=April 12, 2013}}</ref>
