'''Mary Hynes''' is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] radio and television broadcaster. Formerly associated with [[TVOntario]], including the programs ''[[Imprint (TV series)|Imprint]]'' and ''[[Studio 2]]'', which  she co-hosted with [[Steve Paikin]]<ref name="sal1">(4 April 1996). [https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/19186908.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Apr+04%2C+1996&author=By+Sid+Adilman+TORONTO+STAR&pub=Toronto+Star&desc=Studio+2+co-host+Hynes+reports+%24102%2C000+salary&pqatl=google Studio 2 co-host Hynes reports $102,000 salary], ''Toronto Star''</ref> during its first two seasons (1994–95 and 1995–96), she currently hosts the weekly documentary series ''[[Tapestry (CBC radio)|Tapestry]]'' on [[CBC Radio One]].<ref name="Bio1">[http://www.cbc.ca/programguide/personality/mary_hynes Mary Hynes], CBC, Retrieved January 31, 2011</ref><ref name="cbcradio1">(24 August 1989). [https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/470822941.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Aug+24%2C+1989&author=&pub=Toronto+Star&desc=New+hosts+on+CBC+radio&pqatl=google New hosts on CBC radio], ''Toronto Star'' ("On the AM network Mary Hynes takes over hosting duties on Inside Track Sept 9 ...")</ref>

